  "prompt": "What qualification do you need for a nursing job?",
  "response": "To become a nurse, you typically need:\n\n1. Educational Requirements:\n- High school diploma or GED\n- Nursing degree (Associate's or Bachelor's)\n- Nursing program from an accredited institution\n- Common degrees: ADN (Associate Degree in Nursing) or BSN (Bachelor of Science in Nursing)\n\n2. Licensing:\n- Pass the NCLEX-RN (National Council Licensure Examination)\n- Obtain state nursing license\n\n3. Optional Advanced Qualifications:\n- Master's degree (MSN)\n- Specialized certifications\n- Advanced Practice Registered Nurse (APRN) credentials\n\n4. Additional Requirements:\n- CPR certification\n- Background check\n- Physical examination\n- Immunization records\n\n5. Skills:\n- Strong communication\n- Emotional stability\n- Physical stamina\n- Attention to detail\n- Compassion\n\nSpecific requirements can vary by state and type of nursing position (hospital, clinic, specialized care).",
